									"numinlets" : 1,
									"numoutlets" : 0,
									"patching_rect" : [ 48.0, 207.0, 856.0, 114.0 ],
									"text" : "For day-to-day use in Max 9, sfizz~ loads an .sfz with read, reloads it with readagain\n\nYou can trigger it with MIDI note number in the left inlet with velocity in the right inlet, so makenote works directly\n\n—or  triggerwith raw MIDI bytes via midievent. Max also supports a sfizz-specific high-resolution velocity extension: if the third value in midievent is a float, it is interpreted from 0 to 1. \n\n"
								}

							}
, 							{
								"box" : 								{
									"id" : "obj-2",
									"linecount" : 5,
									"maxclass" : "comment",
									"numinlets" : 1,
									"numoutlets" : 0,
									"patching_rect" : [ 42.0, 82.0, 884.0, 74.0 ],
									"text" : "SFZ file sample references are expected relative to the SFZ file’s location (make sure your samples and the .sfz are in the same folder)\n\nThe SFZ output opcode is honored: output=0 routes to channels 1–2, output=1 routes to 3–4, and the object can expose from 2 up to 1024 outputs. \n\nFor large channelizing of output use mc.sfizz~ "
								}

							}
 ],
						"lines" : [  ]
					}
,
